# Buraly, Kaltasinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Buraly (; , BuralÄ±) is a rural locality (a village) in Nizhnekachmashevsky Selsoviet, Kaltasinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 34 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Buraly is located 5 km west of Kaltasy (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kaltasy is the nearest rural locality.
